istribute helpful, useful, non-sale content to your audience. You can quickly achieve this with an <a href=\"https:\/\/umbrellaxact.com\/service\/email-marketing\/\">email marketing agency<\/a>. By using the right tools of your own, you can ensure that your messages reach as many people as possible.<\/p>\n<p><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-788\" src=\"https:\/\/umbrellaxact.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/Email-Marketing-Infographic-1.png\" alt=\"Basics of Email Marketing\" width=\"1024\" height=\"768\" srcset=\"https:\/\/umbrellaxact.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/Email-Marketing-Infographic-1.png 1024w, https:\/\/umbrellaxact.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/Email-Marketing-Infographic-1-300x225.png 300w, https:\/\/umbrellaxact.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/Email-Marketing-Infographic-1-768x576.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" \/><\/p>\n<p>First off, the most important thing about an email marketing campaign is that it must be targeted. There are many different ways to target your potential clients, but the most popular and effective are email campaigns targeting your targeted market and your target market\u2019s demographics. Your emails will have to reach out to them because otherwise, the email message could end up bouncing back to you.<\/p>\n<p>Emails also include special offers, coupons, sales, and contests so that people will keep coming back to see what the latest in products is.<\/p>\n<p>The best part of being on an email list is that you can choose the messages you want to be sent. If you\u2019re going to do something for them, you can let them know. If you want them to buy something, you can let them know. And if you want them to sign up for a newsletter, you can let them know.<\/p>\n<p>With the help of an <a href=\"https:\/\/umbrellaxact.com\/service\/email-marketing\/\">email marketing agency<\/a>, you can make sure that everything you send is targeted and gives your clients an immediate solution for their needs.<\/p>\n<h3>What to do once your emails are sent?<\/h3>\n<p>An email marketing campaign does not just end when the email is sent. It\u2019s important that you keep in touch with your customers after the campaign is over, just as you would expect them to keep you informed about everything that is going on within your business.<\/p>\n<p>You can create newsletters, keep them informed about new products, events, updates, or promotions, or just give them information to help them stay on top of things.<\/p>\n<p>With a good email management software, you can set the time and date on which to send your messages to your subscribers and even schedule other emails as well. You can also schedule when to send them the same message every day.<\/p>\n<p>With a software package like this, it makes it easy to keep track of your messages. You can even set up autoresponders and even schedule outbound autoresponder messages to send out.<\/p>\n<p>If you want to run a successful email campaign without email management software, you can still get the same benefits with the help of an agency. You need to find a <a href=\"https:\/\/umbrellaxact.com\/service\/email-marketing\/\">reliable email marketing agency<\/a> and use them to send your messages. They will take care of the rest, from sending your messages, setting the time and date on which you send them, scheduling them and so on.<\/p>\n<p>Using an email marketing agency for your email marketing campaign is the best choice if you want to be sure that your emails reach your target market in the most effective way possible. Email marketing is a great way to generate business. Email marketing is a way of making your product available to millions of people all over the world.<\/p>\n<p><iframe src=\"https:\/\/www.youtube.com\/embed\/RkiX6zcjJBk\" width=\"560\" height=\"315\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"><\/iframe><br \/>\nSo the question that stares us is how do we decide which agency to hire?<\/p>\n<p>Here are five factors which you should always look in an agency before hiring them:<\/p>\n<p><strong>Structure:<\/strong> Every business is unique in their way, and one size does not fit them all. It holds true for email marketing and hence look for an agency that can provide you with short term and long term plans about your campaigns.<\/p>\n<p><strong>Experience:<\/strong> An experienced email marketing agency will always know what buttons to push and when. It is always challenging to find email leads specific to your niche. Therefore, the email marketing agency will take the initiative to find out who they are, how to contact them, what products they might be interested in, and then send an email to them.<\/p>\n<p><strong>Mobile-Friendly Templates:<\/strong> According to a 2015 study by <a href=\"https:\/\/www.forbes.com\/sites\/louiscolumbus\/2015\/01\/15\/key-take-aways-from-salesforces-2015-state-of-marketing-report\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">state of marketing<\/a>, Responsive design can lead to a 130 per cent increase in email clicks, and that is huge in an industry where people make a killing out of single-digit conversions. Mobile-Friendly email designs will make sure that your text and images open smoothly across all devices, which further increases your viewership.<\/p>\n<p><strong>Add-on services:<\/strong> The most common reason why companies hire email marketing agencies is that they are not able or don\u2019t have the time to produce strategic communication bits. A full-service email marketing agency can do that for you. Hence when you start looking for an agency, also look on the side for services like copywriting, customized graphic design, HTML coding A\/B testing etc.<\/p>\n<p>In addition to the things mentioned earlier, an email marketing agency will have other tools that you will want to use. These include automatic follow-ups and email reminders. This ensures that no matter what, you will always know t